  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dda \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dba\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca 15000\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "15000 metric tons of urea for tea cultivation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Minister Mahinda Amaraweera said that today it was decided to provide 15,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer for tea cultivation.",
        "The Minister, who was sworn in as the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources of the new government, went to the Ministry of Agriculture this afternoon and discussed the distribution of urea fertilizer and the fuel requirements for it and resumed his duties.",
        "A group of officials including the two ministry secretaries participated in this discussion. The minister mentioned that the government decided to provide 15,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer for tea cultivation out of the 65,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer provided by the Indian government under a loan scheme at the request of the Ministry of Plantation Industry.",
        "The Minister also mentioned that President Ranil Wickramasinghe advised the Cabinet that in the future, in the release of fuel, steps will be taken to give priority to the fuel required for food production.",
        "The presidents of the two government-owned fertilizer companies informed the minister that out of the 44,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer that our country has received, nearly 60 percent has been distributed.",
        "The Minister advised to produce a special mixed fertilizer for vegetable cultivation very quickly and arrange to supply that fertilizer to the market within the next two weeks.",
        "Speaking to the media, the minister stated that he is also of the position that everyone should give the new president a fair amount of time to work."
      ],
